<document xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:z="http://www.ebi.ac.uk/z" source="Whatizit"><text><SENT sid="0" pm="."><plain><z:mp ids='MP_0004027'>Trisomy</z:mp> 8 is the most common numerical chromosomal abnormality in <z:hpo ids='HP_0002863'>myelodysplastic syndromes</z:hpo> (<z:e sem="disease" ids="AmbiguousAbbrv" disease_type="AmbiguousAbbrv" abbrv="ambiguous">MDS</z:e>) </plain></SENT>
<SENT sid="1" pm="."><plain><z:e sem="disease" ids="C0024790" disease_type="Disease or Syndrome" abbrv="PNH">Paroxysmal nocturnal haemoglobinuria</z:e> (<z:e sem="disease" ids="AmbiguousAbbrv" disease_type="AmbiguousAbbrv" abbrv="ambiguous">PNH</z:e>) is an aquired <z:hpo ids='HP_0001878'>haemolytic anaemia</z:hpo>, clonal in nature, due to <z:hpo ids='HP_0001428'>somatic mutation</z:hpo> </plain></SENT>
<SENT sid="2" pm="."><plain><z:e sem="disease" ids="AmbiguousAbbrv" disease_type="AmbiguousAbbrv" abbrv="ambiguous">PNH</z:e> may evolve to aplastic <z:hpo ids='HP_0001903'>anaemia</z:hpo>, to <z:e sem="disease" ids="AmbiguousAbbrv" disease_type="AmbiguousAbbrv" abbrv="ambiguous">MDS</z:e> or to <z:hpo ids='HP_0011009'>acute</z:hpo> <z:mpath ids='MPATH_342'>myeloid leukaemia</z:mpath> </plain></SENT>
<SENT sid="3" pm="."><plain>We present a patient who had <z:mp ids='MP_0004027'>trisomy</z:mp> 8 mosaicism at disease presentation who received therapy with <z:hpo ids='HP_0000001'>all</z:hpo>-trans-<z:chebi fb="2" ids="26536">retinoic acid</z:chebi>, responded to therapy, and developed <z:e sem="disease" ids="AmbiguousAbbrv" disease_type="AmbiguousAbbrv" abbrv="ambiguous">PNH</z:e> in the course of the disease </plain></SENT>
<SENT sid="4" pm="."><plain>Cytogenetics at the time of <z:e sem="disease" ids="AmbiguousAbbrv" disease_type="AmbiguousAbbrv" abbrv="ambiguous">PNH</z:e> diagnosis showed a <z:mpath ids='MPATH_458'>normal</z:mpath> karyotype </plain></SENT>
</text></document>